  "active_lock_reason": null,
  "body": "## Issue\r\n\r\nIt would be quite useful for the codec (or users of the codec) if there were a method that allowed one to get all the project's artifacts (say as an array).  These could just be artifacts or they could be whole constructor objects like `artifacts.require` returns; I guess the latter would be more convenient.  It could be called `artifacts.requireAll` or something similar.  This would allow one to use the codec without having to always first manually get all the artifacts you need.\r\n\r\n## Expected Behavior\r\n\r\nThis method should exist.\r\n\r\n## Actual Results\r\n\r\nNo such method currently exists.",
